character actor</link>. </p>
<p>

Though he has been a working actor since the 1950s, Kirby is most familiar to <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../762/256762.xml">
Columbo</link></series>
</it> fans as the gullible Sergeant Kramer. He also appeared in the 1971 movie called <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../221/14754221.xml">
How to Frame a Figg</link></movie>
</it> with <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../774/269774.xml">
Don Knotts</link></actor>
</person>
. A notable recent appearance was as Pop Ryan, father of Officer John Ryan (played by <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../514/423514.xml">
Matt Dillon</link></actor>
) in the 2004 film <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../535/1749535.xml">
Crash</link></movie>
</it>.</p>
